{"request_type": "daily_briefing", "response": "Yesterday's data is a bit patchy across the board—looks like May 14th didn't get logged in several places, so I'm working with what I have through May 11th.

The good news is the trend is solid. Your weight has dropped 2 pounds over the month with real momentum in early May, and you're backing that up with genuine consistency: 28 days of activity in 30, mixing walks, weight training, swimming, and everything else. That's not casual commitment. The food picture is straightforward too—you've got a rhythm of structured, nutritious meals punctuated by indulgent days (those root beer float burgers are clearly a favorite), and somehow it's working. The weight's coming down anyway.

On the learning and gaming fronts, you've been steady but low-key. You're working through AWS and MLOps stuff, halfway through The Martian, and gaming lightly with a nice mix of roguelikes and strategy games when you do sit down. Nothing dramatic, but nothing stalled either. It reads like you're maintaining a bunch of interests without burning out on any single one. That's actually harder to sustain than it sounds."}
